Name: pylandau
Version: 2.1.0
Summary: A Landau PDF definition to be used in Python.
Home-page: https://github.com/SiLab-Bonn/pyLandau
Author: David-Leon Pohl
Author-email: pohl@physik.uni-bonn.de
Maintainer: David-Leon Pohl
Maintainer-email: pohl@physik.uni-bonn.de
License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 2.1
Keywords: Landau,Langau,PDF
Platform: any
Requires-Dist: cython
Requires-Dist: numpy

The Landau propability density function is defined in C++ and made available to python via cython. Also a fast Gaus+Landau convolution is available. The interface accepts numpy arrays.


